title: For Sale/Trade:  FNH 5.7
postcontent: The FN 5.7 is a pistol of it's own class. Of course made by FNH. It is a very well engineered pistol. Even though it looks like a plastic toy gun and when you hold it... it feels like a toy gun, but this pistol is a gun any gun enthusiast must have. There's a reason it's featured so much in call of duty mw3 or black ops 2, because the gun holds 20 rounds, absolutely NO recoil, it's accurate up to 100 yards no problem, and that's not being some pro on "TopShot" even though it may seem like it. The gun shoots the 5.7x28 round. It's basically a shortened 5.56 round made for a pistol. The clips even load like an AR15 magazine. When shot the bullet acts like a rifle round so it gives it excellent range, excellent accuracy, and excellent stopping power with no recoil and 20 shots. They've been wanting to limit this pistol to military use only for a while now so better act quick before it's banned along with the 2nd amendment. I will take trades or cash offers. Don't ask me how much, or ask what i want to trade for. Make offers! I prefer things unique.

title: For Sale:  FS: HK USP Compact 40 S&W LEM V7 w/ 3 Hi-cap Mags
postcontent: Sigs and Glocks are fine for most people, but  "In a world of compromise some men don't."  -Heckler & Koch.  The HK USP Compact is the smaller version of the pistol SEAL UDTs refused to give up when the Navy tried to replace them with Sigs.  I am selling one of my two ( so nice I bought it twice ) HK USP Compact 40 S&W Variant 7 Law Enforcement Modification DAO with a bobbed hammer, since I recently purchased a USP Expert.  In wake for the '86 FBI shootout in Miami, the 40 S&W was developed to pack the energy of most 45ACP loads to replace 9mm, yet still allow high capacity and more compact form factors.  The LEM V7 is not a true DAO, since once the slide is racked it acts like a SA, but the hammer rests forward like it is uncocked and the trigger pull is very light.  If you aren't familiar with HK LEM, checkout: http://pistol-training.com/articles/hk-lem-vs-sig-dak  The pistol I am selling is not the one for carry, so it has only very light wear.  It comes with night sights, soft sided case and 3 hi-capacity 12 round magazines, so you get 12+1 .  If you aren't familiar, the V7 LEM does not have a safety, but it is easy to add one.  Ohio ID required, CCW preferred.   $600/obo

title: For Sale:  Gun Ban Bills SB 5737 & Diane Feinstein's Gun Ban Bill
postcontent:
WA state SB 5737 is a bill to ban "assault weapons". Originally, the wording  of Senate Bill 5737 included an annual inspection at your home: 

“In order to continue to possess an assault weapon that was legally possessed on the effective date of this section, the person possessing shall ... safely and securely store the assault weapon. The sheriff of the county may, no more than once per year, conduct an inspection to ensure compliance with this subsection.”

http://www.thehighroad.org/showthread.php?t=703933

Meaning the police would have the right to come in to your home an inspect your assault rifle to make sure you were complying with their law.

However, it seems the offending paragraph has been removed and the bill now seeks to completely outlaw simultaneous possession of semiautomatic or pump action rifle (!), pistols and shotguns "capable of accepting a detachable magazine" AND "any magazine capable of use with that firearm that contains more than ten rounds of ammunition" at the same time.

Read paragraph (2) and decide for yourself:

"NEW SECTION. Sec. 2. A new section is added to chapter 9.41 RCW
 to read as follows:

(2) No person in this state shall possess or have under his or her
control at one time both of the following:
(a) A semiautomatic or pump-action rifle, semiautomatic pistol, or
shotgun capable of accepting a detachable magazine; and
 (b) Any magazine capable of use with that firearm that contains
more than ten rounds of ammunition.

(3) Subsection (1) of this section shall not apply to any of the
following:
(a) The possession of an unloaded assault weapon for the purpose of
permanently relinquishing it to a law enforcement agency in this state. (SB 5737 p. 6)

Apparently, this combination of a semiautomatic (or pump action) firearm (rifle, pistol or shotgun) and a magazine of more than 10 rounds constitutes an "assault rifle", and is therefore bad.

Also, while the bill says it is OK to carry what they apparently consider "assault weapons" to and from a "licensed, lawfully operated shooting range" or target shooting event, it makes no mention of carrying and using such rifles and pistols during a hunting trip. By default, that seems to be illegal.

This bill was sponsored by Ed Murray, Jeanne Kohl-Welles and Adam Kline:

http://www.leg.wa.gov/senate/senators/pages/Murray.aspx

http://www.leg.wa.gov/senate/senators/pages/Kohl-Welles.aspx

http://www.leg.wa.gov/senate/senators/pages/Kline.aspx

Please contact your representative and voice your strong disapproval to SB 5737

http://apps.leg.wa.gov/billinfo/summary.aspx?bill=5737&year=2013

Here is the bill itself. Please read it and understand what they are trying to take away!

http://apps.leg.wa.gov/documents/billdocs/2013-14/Pdf/Bills/Senate%20Bills/5737.pdf

Here is a list of all Washington State Legislators email addresses:

https://dlr.leg.wa.gov/MemberEmail/Default.aspx

Please contact them and voice your support of the 2nd Amendment. Remember, it is your pump-action assault rifle they are trying to ban.

Also, Diane Feinstein is at it again. She hopes to ban all "assault weapons" which are defined as  “semiautomatic, centerfire, or rimfire rifle that has a fixed magazine with the capacity to accept more than 10 rounds,” except for tubular-magazine .22s. Also, any “semiautomatic, centerfire, or rimfire rifle that has an overall length of less than 30 inches,” any “semiautomatic handgun with a fixed magazine that has the capacity to accept more than 10 rounds,” and any semi-automatic handgun that has a threaded barrel.

Further, her bill would require the owners of existing “assault weapons” to register them with the federal government under the National Firearms Act (NFA). The NFA imposes a $200 tax per firearm, and requires an owner to submit photographs and fingerprints to the Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, Firearms and Explosives (BATFE), to inform the BATFE of the address where the firearm will be kept, and to obtain the BATFE’s permission to transport the firearm across state lines. 

Please write your reps and stop this madwoman before she does real harm. Use the NRA's website:

http://www.nraila.org/get-involved-locally/grassroots/write-your-reps.aspx
